text: Nizhny Muynak () is a rural locality (a village) in Muynaksky Selsoviet, Zianchurinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 73 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 36 km from Isyangulovo, 8 km from Verkhny Muynak. == References == Category:Rural localities in Zianchurinsky District
title: Nizhny Muynak
